Layout Managers
Pack: Packs each widgets next to each other in a logical format. Usually, starts from the top. Can be changed by adding a side parameter, E.g, Side="left/bottom/right"

Place: Its all about, Precise Positioning. WHen using place, You can provide a Y and X Value.
I.e, my_label.place(x=0, y=0)
However, Its downside is that its so specific. and becomes tedious when moving multiple widgets

Grid: It imagins that the entire program is a grid that can be divided into any row and columns
Row are horizontal
Columns are Vertical
I.e, my_label.grid(column=0, row=0)
Easier is to define from top left(0,0) then continue from there

